<h3>&AGENT:name; Match Criteria</h3>

<blockquote><em>
  The match criteria specify the transactions in which this agent is
  interested.  A <code>-</code> after a criterion name indicates that the
  criterion must be <em>false</em>; criteria with no value specified must be
  <em>true.</em>  <em>All</em> criteria must be met in order for the agent to
  match and its ``Act-on'' hook (below) to be executed.
</em></blockquote>

<pre><protect result='result' markup='markup'>&AGENT:criteria;</protect></pre>

<h3>&AGENT:name; Agent Act-On Hook</h3>

<blockquote><em>
  This is the code that <a href='/&amp;agentType/&AGENT:name;'>&AGENT:name;</a> runs
  whenever its match criteria are satisfied.  
  It can be customized by making an edited copy of the initialization
  document, <code><a href='/PIA/Agents/&agentType;/&AGENT:name;/initialize'>/PIA/Agents/&agentType;/&AGENT:name;/initialize.??</a></code>, and putting
  it in your personal &AGENT:name; Agent document directory as <code><a href='/~/Agents/&agentType;/&AGENT:name;/initialize'>~/.pia/Agents/&agentType;/&AGENT:name;/initialize.??</a></code> or <code><a href='/~/Agents/&AGENT:name;/initialize'>~/.pia/Agents/&AGENT:name;/initialize.??</a></code>.  The latter is not as
  good because it could get confused with another agent of the same name and a
  different type.  (Replace <code>??</code> in the names above with the
  current one of <code>xh</code> (new) or <code>if</code> (old).)
</em></blockquote>

<pre><protect result='result' markup='markup'>&AGENT:act-on;</protect>
</pre>
